<TEXT>
<P>
Tribune Co.: Net income in the third quarter for the publisher of the Chicago 
Tribune, the New York Daily News and other newspapers was $38.2 million, down 
39% from the same period of 1989, on revenue of $588 million, about the same as 
last year. The Chicago-based company said operating losses in its newsprint 
division and at the Daily News were primarily responsible. 
</P>
