<HEADLINE>
<P>
REPARATIONS TO WAR INTERNEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Now that the Japanese internees have been compensated, how about the same for 
our American Indians. 
</P>
<P>
They lost much more than houses, furniture and a couple years of their lives. 
Their culture was destroyed, their land confiscated and many were killed. Why 
the double standard? 
</P>
<P>
RONALD JOHN EXLEY, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
