<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego police arrested two persons Monday on suspicion of murder in the 
bludgeoning death Friday night of 38-year-old Victor Avena. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Avena was attacked and killed in his home in the 3800 block of 42nd 
Street. Mexican authorities had found his body Sunday night in an isolated spot 
north of Ensenada in Baja California. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested about 12:30 p.m. Monday at a restaurant on Coronado Avenue were 
Avena's wife, Maria Guadalupe Oregal, 23, and her 16-year-old brother, whose 
name was withheld because he is a juvenile. Both had just crossed the border 
into the United States from Mexico. 
</P>
