<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SUPERVISOR HAHN GOES HOME FROM HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Veteran Los Angeles County Supervisor Kenneth Hahn was sent home Monday 
following a three-day hospital stay for what an aide said was a bout with 
flu-like symptoms. 
</P>
<P>
The 70-year-old Hahn, who suffered a stroke in 1987 that left him partially 
paralyzed and in a wheelchair, "is responding well to an adjustment in his 
medication and is expected to rest at home for about one week," said Hahn 
spokeswoman Lynn Sakamoto. 
</P>
<P>
Hahn was admitted to Daniel Freeman Memorial Hospital on Friday complaining of 
"chest discomfort." 
</P>
<P>
"The supervisor did not have a heart attack," Sakamoto said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
