<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Look Who's Talking Now: A 3-year-old boy wonder from Kansas who wowed audiences 
in recent network television interviews is set for his acting debut. 
</P>
<P>
The boy, Seth Kinast, will begin rehearsals Friday for a segment of "Baby 
Talk," the comedy based on the movie "Look Who's Talking," scheduled to debut 
on ABC in November. He'll play a student at a school for young geniuses. The 
3-year-old's reading skills and his abilities to recite the Greek alphabet and 
the English alphabet forward and backward landed him on David Letterman's 
late-night talk show. "Baby Talk" stars Tony Danza and Julia Duffy. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102390-0040 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 296454 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 23, 1990, Tuesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Part F; Page 2; Column 1; Entertainment Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
