<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT; 
</P>
<P>
WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
USC; 
</P>
<P>
SMITH HOLDS EDGE OVER ASU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Arizona State, which will play USC Saturday at Tempe, Ariz., is the only team 
in the Pacific 10 Conference that holds a series edge over the Trojans. The Sun 
Devils are 5-3 against USC in a series that started in 1978. 
</P>
<P>
But Coach Larry Smith is 6-2 against Arizona State, including a 5-2 record 
while he coached at Arizona. Twice, in 1982 and 1985, Smith's Arizona team 
deprived the Sun Devils of a Rose Bowl bid by beating them in the last game of 
the regular season. In the 1986 season, when ASU was 10-1-1 and beat Michigan 
in the Rose Bowl, its only loss was to Arizona. 
</P>
<P>
USC's 35-26 loss to Arizona Saturday was its first in a Pac-10 game at the 
Coliseum in 3 1/2 seasons under Smith. Smith's USC teams are 17-3-1 at the 
Coliseum, 12-1-1 in conference games. JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</TEXT>
