<P>
SAINTS' HILLIARD SUFFERS KNEE INJURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Running back Dalton Hilliard of the New Orleans Saints suffered a torn ligament 
in his right knee late in Sunday's loss to Houston and will be sidelined for at 
least this week's game against Detroit, Coach Jim Mora said. 
</P>
<P>
The early diagnosis indicated Hilliard will recover without surgery and will 
not be sidelined long enough to warrant being placed on injured reserve, Mora 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Rueben Mayes probably will start against Detroit in Hilliard's place, Mora 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Starting center Grant Feasel of the Seattle Seahawks underwent arthroscopic 
surgery on his right knee after being injured in Sunday's victory over Kansas 
City, Coach Chuck Knox said. 
</P>
<P>
Knox said that because the Seahawks have an off-week, they hope to have Feasel 
in the starting lineup Nov. 4 against the San Diego Chargers in the Kingdome. 
Associated Press 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
NATIONAL FOOTBALL LEAGUE; SPORTS INJURIES; FOOTBALL PLAYERS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
