<TEXT>
<P>
U.S. troops in Saudi Arabia may soon be able to listen to something more than 
the desert winds. 
</P>
<P>
Japan plans to send 40,000 Walkman-type cassette players to the troops as part 
of its aid to the multinational forces in the Persian Gulf, the Japan Times 
reported Monday. 
