VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: CONEJO GRADE; 
</P>
<P>
3 INJURED IN CRASH ON VENTURA FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GERRY BRAILO SPENCER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The occupants of a slow-moving vehicle heading south on the Ventura Freeway at 
the Conejo Grade suffered minor injuries after being hit in the rear by another 
vehicle. The passengers were wearing seat belts, the CHP reported. 
</P>
<P>
Dirk Spialti, 20, of Ventura and Jo Ellen Davis of Yucaipa were treated for 
minor injuries Sunday night at Los Robles Regional Medical Center in Thousand 
Oaks and released. 
</P>
<P>
The CHP said witnesses reported that the driver of the second vehicle, Kenneth 
Daugherty, 55, of Monterey Park, was traveling about 55 to 60 m.p.h. in the 
slow lane near the truck scales and braked before hitting Spialti, who was 
traveling about 10 to 15 m.p.h. 
</P>
<P>
Daugherty was not wearing a seat belt, officials said. He suffered major 
injuries and was also taken to Los Robles Regional Medical Center, where he is 
reported in fair condition. GERRY BRAILO SPENCER 
</P>
