<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bar Assn., Business Groups Agree: Colorado businesses will try to slash legal 
costs and reduce off-the-job time losses by attempting negotiation and 
mediation before taking their disagreements to court, under a newly introduced 
program. 
</P>
<P>
The program, called "Colorado Pledge," is an agreement by the bar association, 
the Greater Denver Chamber of Commerce, the Colorado Assn. of Commerce and 
Industry and the National Federation of Independent Business, Conover told 
reporters. "We hope it will show to you a side of lawyers that is not 
frequently enough publicized -- a side of lawyers that solves problems and 
helps clients solve problems not in the courtroom arena," Bar Assn. President 
Jerry Conover. 
