<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: 2ND-QUARTER NET INCOME SOARS 266% FOR AMGEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Amgen Inc., a Thousand Oaks biotechnology company, said its net income soared 
266% to $14.3 million in the second quarter that ended Sept. 30 from $3.9 
million a year before. Amgen attributed the huge jump to sales of its drug for 
the treatment of chronic anemia in kidney dialysis patients. 
</P>
<P>
The drug, called Epogen, was approved for sale by the Food and Drug 
Administration in June, 1989. Amgen said its total revenues for the second 
quarter nearly doubled to $78.8 million, from $39.6 million last year. 
</P>
<P>
For the first half of Amgen's fiscal year, the company's profit increased more 
than fivefold to $25.5 million, from $4.7 million a year ago. Amgen's six 
months' sales more than doubled to $150.5 million, from $68.1 million. 
</P>
