Man Arraigned in Theft of GM Pictures: Authorities arrested a former photo 
technician for General Motors Corp. on charges he tried to get the auto maker 
to pay $75,000 for stolen confidential photographs of GM cars. Gregory Charles 
Hooper, 36, of Royal Oak, Mich., was charged with mail fraud in a complaint 
