<TEXT>
<P>
AT&amp;T to Raise Long-Distance Rates: American Telephone &amp; Telegraph will 
raise its basic night and weekend long-distance phone prices by 2.2% beginning 
Nov. 2, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
The company said the increase will result in about $39.4 million in increased 
annual revenue. That amounts to about five cents on an average $16 monthly 
long-distance bill. AT&amp;T said the increase applies only to out-of-state 
direct-dialed long distance calls made during night and weekend hours. These 
are after 11 p.m. Sunday through Friday and all weekend until 5 p.m. Sunday. 
