shark, which scientists consider harmless to humans. PAUL DE BAETS / For The 
Times; Photo, COLOR, Small-boat operators -- and an unfazed dog -- look on as 
the shark is towed from Dana Point Harbor back out to sea, where it was filmed, 
tagged and released. ; Photo, (A2) Culture Shark: A megamouth shark -- a 
mysterious species -- caught Sunday was released back into the waters off Dana 
Point after researchers videotaped him underwater and implanted two radio 
transmitters to track his movements. Above, the shark is towed out to sea. MARK 
BOSTER / Los Angeles Times; Photo, COLOR, A crowd of people hoping to glimpse 
the rare shark gathered along the docks. ; Photo, COLOR, The megamouth, tied by 
