faces white to signify number of drug-related deaths each day in United States, 
below. DAVID MURONAKA / Los Angeles Times; Photo, COLOR, Senior Larisa Moore, 
17, was among the students whose faces were painted white to signify a 
drug-related death as part of Red Ribbon Week at Capistrano Valley High School. 
</P>
