<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE MAN CRUSHED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SOUTH GATE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 40-year-old Garden Grove man was killed Monday when the hydraulic unit of a 
forklift fell and crushed him, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Bleigh Merrell was working at Mann Aircraft Forming Co., located on 
Firestone Place, when the accident occurred about 1:30 p.m., said South Gate 
Police Lt. Russell Beecher. 
</P>
<P>
Merrell was looking underneath the forklift to see why it was not working when 
the lift mechanism fell on top of him, Beecher said. He was pronounced dead at 
the scene. 
</P>
</TEXT>
