<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE ADDS 5 MORE FREEWAY SOUNDWALLS TO LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Transportation Commission recently added five more freeway 
soundwalls to the list of 13 already scheduled for construction in Orange 
County. 
</P>
<P>
In some cases, residents have waited 20 years after their homes were built for 
the state to approve the soundwalls, which include: 
</P>
<P>
* A $3.9-million soundwall along the Riverside Freeway between East Street and 
State College Boulevard in Anaheim due in 1994-95. 
</P>
<P>
* A $2.2-million wall on the Orange Freeway between Yorba Linda Boulevard and 
Rolling Hills Drive in Fullerton also due in 1994-95. 
</P>
<P>
* A $1.6-million wall on the Garden Grove Freeway between Beach Boulevard and 
Yockey Street in Garden Grove scheduled for 1995-96. 
</P>
<P>
* A $1.8-million wall along the Santa Ana Freeway between Ball Road and Lincoln 
Avenue in Anaheim slated for 1996-97. 
</P>
<P>
* A $3.1-million wall between the San Gabriel River Freeway and homes on Martha 
Ann Drive in Rossmoor, where ground will be broken soon. 
</P>
<P>
Of the 13 walls previously given state priority, three are under design by a 
consultant hired by the Orange County Transportation Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
WALLS; SOUND; FREEWAYS; ORANGE COUNTY -- TRANSPORTATION 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
