<HEADLINE>
<P>
VILLA PARK DEFEATS EL TORO IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kip Parsons and Neal Brockmeier each had three goals to lead Villa Park High 
School, the sixth-ranked water polo team in Orange County, to a 12-8 victory 
over fourth-ranked El Toro in a nonleague game Monday at Villa Park. 
</P>
<P>
Villa Park (16-6) led, 5-4, at halftime and outscored El Toro (16-6) 4-0 in the 
third quarter to take control. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Bowman had 11 saves for Villa Park. 
</P>
</TEXT>
