<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURE ALLIANCE, PLATING COMPANY MERGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Venture Alliance Group of Santa Ana and Prime Plating Inc. of Los Angeles 
announced their merger Monday and said the new entity would focus on the 
acquisition and consolidation of electroplating firms. 
</P>
<P>
The new company, Prime Industries of Santa Ana, will employ about 90 people and 
have annual revenues of more than $3 million. 
</P>
<P>
Rudy A. Berti, president and chief executive of the new firm, said he plans to 
bring technical and waste management expertise to the electroplating industry, 
which he described as "crippled with poorly managed companies." He said many 
firms are hurt by a lack of self-regulation and by a lack of knowledge of 
federal environmental requirements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
