<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Menendez ruling -- An Oct. 11 digest item in The Times regarding the murder 
case of brothers Lyle and Erik Menendez may have been unclear. 
</P>
<P>
Superior Court Judge James Albracht said that, in ruling that audiotapes made 
by psychologist Jerome Oziel are not confidential, he determined that Oziel had 
divulged information about his sessions with the brothers to a third party to 
avert threatened danger. From the bench, Albracht did not name the third party. 
However, he said in an interview that Judalon Smyth was the only witness 
besides Oziel who testified at the hearings on the tapes. Smyth and Oziel have 
acknowledged that they had an affair. 
</P>
