<P>
GRANADA HILLS PILOT MISSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Authorities are searching for a 68-year-old Granada Hills man who has been 
missing since Monday morning when he took off in his single-engine plane from 
Whiteman Airport. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Bell, a retired carpenter, told his family Monday that he was going to 
Whiteman in Pacoima to look at a plane, said Detective Jim Lewis of the Los 
Angeles Police Department's Missing Persons unit. 
</P>
<P>
When Bell failed to return home, his wife called police, who discovered Bell's 
plane was missing from its hangar and his car parked nearby, Lewis said. Police 
believe that Bell took off in his plane on an impromptu pleasure ride over the 
Mojave Desert, as is often his custom, Lewis said. 
</P>
<P>
Tuesday morning, eight planes combed the desert in search of Bell, said Lt. 
Kate Kelley, a spokeswoman for the Civil Air Patrol. 
</P>
