<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE'S PHARMACY: NITROUS OXIDE CANISTERS GIVE A 'HIGH' FEELING BUT CAN KILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOE GRAEDON and TERESA GRAEDON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: I work in a store that sells a device for whipping cream. We also 
sell the chargers, which contain nitrous oxide (laughing gas). 
</P>
<P>
Our problem is customers who buy the chargers for recreational purposes. It's 
not unusual for a group of teen-agers to request 10 boxes on a Friday or a 
Saturday night. (A box contains 10 chargers.) 
</P>
<P>
We are upset about this because we are aware that abuse can be dangerous and 
that people have died of overdoses. Please tell us how this gas affects the 
brain and why people die from inhaling it. 
</P>
<P>
Answer: Nitrous oxide has been used as an anesthetic for more than 100 years 
and is still used during surgery under carefully controlled conditions because 
it is an analgesic. Unfortunately, "laughing gas" has also been abused because 
it produces a "high" feeling. 
</P>
<P>
The problem with inhaling nitrous oxide is that it can cause unconsciousness 
due to lack of oxygen. A person who overdoses may stop breathing. 
</P>
<P>
You have a legitimate concern about the abuse of the nitrous oxide canisters 
used for whipping cream. Perhaps the store could consider limiting the number 
of chargers it sells to minors. 
</P>
<P>
Q: What can I do for itching of the anus? I have had it for some time, and it 
is driving me crazy. This biting and itching feeling is embarrassing, and most 
of the time the drugstore hemorrhoid remedies don't stop it. 
</P>
<P>
A: Dermatologists tell us that pruritus ani, also known as itchy bottom, can be 
caused by many factors. Coffee, citrus fruit and beans may aggravate this 
condition, as can tight clothing. Perfumed toilet paper and clothes washed in 
fabric softener also may contribute. People who are overweight are more likely 
to suffer. 
</P>
<P>
The usual remedies are greasy ointments or cortisone creams. These are likely 
to make the problem worse because they increase moisture in the area. Although 
it is difficult, try to avoid scratching, as it can set up a vicious cycle that 
leads to more intense itching. 
</P>
<P>
A dermatologist may be able to determine the underlying cause. In the meantime, 
keep the area dry by patting it clean with cotton balls soaked in witch hazel 
or special wipes such as Tucks, Mediconet or Preparation H Cleansing Pads. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102390-0173 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 296981 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 23, 1990, Tuesday, P.M. Final 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Part P; Page 10; Column 1; Late Final Desk 
</P>
